{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":13647,"record_hash":"sha256:a147b3ffd160006446d9e0ed5c6d1aa2ea52970c9c5929cb8cbcf8a25dc3a4dc","timestamp":"2026-05-09T16:46:30.366Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"assistant","text":"It is contained inside one GitMeta list entry, not stored as many separate metadata keys.\n\nConcretely, for a session prefix like:\n\n```text\nmeta:local:gitbutler:agent-session:codex:<session-key>\n```\n\nthere is one list key:\n\n```text\nmeta:local:gitbutler:agent-session:codex:<session-key>:transcript\n```\n\nEach transcript record is appended to that list as one JSON string envelope:\n\n```text\n:transcript = [\n  \"{ envelope for transcript record 0 }\",\n  \"{ envelope for transcript record 1 }\",\n  \"{ envelope for transcript record 2 }\"\n]\n```\n\nInside each envelope is the normalized record metadata plus the redacted original parsed provider record:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"source_record_index\": 0,\n  \"source_record_hash\": \"sha256:...\",\n  \"source_event_kind\": \"response_item\",\n  \"turn_id\": \"turn-1\",\n  \"role\": \"assistant\",\n  \"source_record\": {\n    \"type\": \"response_item\",\n    \"payload\": {\n      \"turn_id\": \"turn-1\",\n      \"role\": \"assistant\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nSo:\n\n```text\nGitMeta key\n  :transcript\n      list entry 0 -> JSON envelope containing transcript record 0\n      list entry 1 -> JSON envelope containing transcript record 1\n      list entry 2 -> JSON envelope containing transcript record 2\n```\n\nThe separate GitMeta entries like `:provider`, `:model`, `:source-sha256`, `:seen-record-hashes` are session-level metadata. The per-transcript-record content lives inside the `:transcript` list.","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-09T16:46:30.366Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}